{"author":{"id":"783b610f274a0d93f6239db0fc75d0982606c877a4661d3aea84b42bc3a85cea"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1634584915,"nonce":"IdgS8kk2bvI9CS590nW+N8vNspg=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOAW4Y0s49XQHC","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/4087","origin":"github"},"title":"Fasta Statistics v 1.0.3 breaks the first time it is executed on multiple compressed fasta data inputs","message":"Not sure if this is a Galaxy, ToolShed, or tool problem. Maybe is both a UI problem in 21.09 and some underlying problem with the MTS or Tool. Can reproduce/compare at both ORG and EU. \n\nTool: https://toolshed.g2.bx.psu.edu/view/iuc/fasta_stats/56022eb50bbd\n\nTo reproduce:\n1. Two fasta.gz datasets\n2. Multi-select both input datasets\n3. ORG successful: The _first-time run_ creates a \"null\" output dataset number for the first output + the \"next\" dataset number for the second output (eg: doesn't skip any dataset numbers due to the null). The _second-time run_ creates both outputs as expected.\n4. EU fails (?): Same first/second run behavior re \"null\" but results in errored datasets\n5. Both \"null\" and \"success\" datasets have this message in Job info `\"my\" variable $thresh masks earlier declaration in same scope at /cvmfs/main.galaxyproject.org/shed_tools/toolshed.g2.bx.psu.edu/repos/iuc/fasta_stats/56022eb50bbd/fasta_stats/fasta-stats.pl line 68.`\n\nCode (perl script):\nhttps://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/blob/master/tools/fasta_stats/fasta-stats.pl#L68\n\nTest histories:\n* ORG version 'Galaxy version 21.09.rc1, commit b0f1fe805df2caec377a9504cde8f42f7d6558d5' https://usegalaxy.org/u/jen-galaxyproject/h/test-fasta-stats-v103\n* EU version 'Galaxy version 21.05' (not sure where to capture commit) https://usegalaxy.eu/u/jenj/h/test-fasta-stats-v103\n\nScreenshots. Slightly different between the servers.\n\n**ORG**\n\nHow the tool form displays when multi-select is initially clicked on\n\u003cimg width=\"1180\" alt=\"Screen Shot 202